HOW TO USE

cc2 will always try to create a directory to write all generated files. We refer to this directory
as ComDir (Comment Directory). The ComDir will always contain the following data:
	- output.html		The actual HTML output which will display the generated facebook comment in a browser
	- data/				cc2 copies all needed files (such as images and styles) in this directory
		- data/image/	All used images. Note: The image "kundendienst.png" will always be in this directory
		- data/site/	All images used in the comment template are stored in this directory

-c		Create				Create a ComDir
-ca		Create all			Create multiple comdirs from a base directory
-i 		Input				Set input type (default: json)
							Possible input types:
								- json
								- txt
-debug	Debug information	Prints more debug information